  <brief_title>Objective Assessment of Physical Activity in Older Adults</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Universitaire Ziekenhuizen Leuven</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Universitaire Ziekenhuizen Leuven</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the present study is to evaluate the validity of 2 objective measures of
      physical activity among older adults. In addition, the investigators will examine the
      influence of functionality, walking aids, walking speed and step length on the accuracy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
